<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO LETTERS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jan  9 22:57:12 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I am a senior at California State University Dominguez Hills, I am doing a paper on PTSD and my topic is PTSD among Vietnam Veterns.  The stories I have just read are not only helpful but very heartfelt.  I was not born when the war was going on but I do feel some of the things you are going through just by reading these stoies.  All of you were and are brave men and women, you should never think otherwise.  I myself have and still are one of the many people who experience PTSD, I lost my mother when I was very young and soon after was diagnosed with PTSD.  Sometimes I think they just diagnose a person with the disease because they have nothing else to do.  My hearts go out to you.
<p><code>--   (kelly) </code><p>


